.SH "IPMIMONITORING OPTIONS"
The following options are specific to
.B Ipmimonitoring.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase verbosity in output.  This option will output additional
sensors that are generally unreadable or uninterpretable.
#include <@top_srcdir@/common/man/manpage-common-sensor-common.man>
#include <@top_srcdir@/common/man/manpage-common-interpret-oem-data.man>
.TP
\fB\-\-ignore\-non\-interpretable\-sensors\fR
Ignore non-interpretable sensors in output.  Although usually
identical, this is semantically different that the
\fB\-\-ignore\-na\-sensors\fR option in
.B ipmi-sensors(8).
For example, if an interpretation rule has not been written for a
sensor, it may not be output.
